Médaille du Maroc. Authorized in 1909, for all who took part in the military operation in that country, or in protecting property there. The ribbon for this is similar to the Médaille Coloniale, but in green with one wide and two narrow white stripes. The bars given with this medal are for 
   Casablanca, Oudjda, Haut-Guir, Fez;
 and many others have since been added.
